        "content": "<p>I can't find in the documentation how to repeatedly compose a function in the documentation.<br>\nFor example, there is no way to rewrite</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f</span> <span class=\"bp\">∘</span> <span class=\"n\">f</span> <span class=\"bp\">∘</span> <span class=\"n\">f</span> <span class=\"o\">)</span> <span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"bp\">=</span> <span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">f</span> <span class=\"bp\">^</span> <span class=\"mi\">3</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>  <span class=\"n\">x</span> <span class=\"c1\">--or maybe in some other notation because the RHS is interpreted as (f x) ^ 3</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>and no already defined way for arbitrarily many compositions. <br>\nDoes this type of thing already exist?</p>",
